{
  "texts": [
    "The rest were other non-ACS diseases with chest pain manifestations.",
    "Among the cases misdiagnosed as ACS by the \"Lingyi Zhihui\", the average proportion of cases that were eventually diagnosed as acute aortic dissection was approximately 9.14% (95% CI: 8.83%-9.44%).",
    "The average proportion of patients who were eventually diagnosed with acute pulmonary embolism was 2.83% (95% CI: 2.63%-3.03%).",
    "Although human experts presented higher accuracy, there were still some cases misdiagnosed.",
    "Among the total cases misdiagnosed as ACS by human experts, acute aortic dissection accounted for 5.27% (95% CI: 4.80%-5.74%) and acute pulmonary embolism accounted for 0.96% (95% CI: 0.74%-1.18%)."
  ]
}